actions.thought:
River Ad pairs the ace, upgrading my hand from middle pair top kicker to top two pair (AA KK) with a 9 kicker, on a paired kings board (Ks Kc). Heads-up OOP vs Claude (deep 19k, LAG UTG raiser with history of multi-street aggression: e.g., Hands #6, #29, #37, #52 barrelling profitably). Pot 6550, my stack 5825 (~0.9 SPR). Previous plan check-call turn with ~40% equity expecting value-heavy polarized range (AK/KQ/KJs+/sets/bluffs like QJ/JT/AQ); river dynamics shift unfavorably: 
- Value range (high %): AK/KQ/KJ/KT all make kings full/trips+ (beats us); KK/99/77/ K9 crush (full houses); 
- Former bluffs/Ax now often top two with better kicker (AJ+/AT+ beat our kicker); 
- Pure air (QJ/JT/OTD) ~20-30% range we beat, but many check back/ bet small. 
Equity now ~25-35% (beats narrow bluff slice, loses to 65-75% range), < pot odds for typical bet (e.g., 2-3k bet needs ~25% direct). OOP check-fold optimal: preserves stack for better spots (tournament mid-stage, 90 hands left, 6 active); induces bluffs rarely but avoids bloating/coolers; betting risks raise-fold to better Kx (~50% fold equity not enough vs LAG calls), thin value from missed draws. Consistent with speculative BB defense turning marginal post-turn; fold > hero-call OOP vs 3-street agg on dry-turned-scare board. Long-term EV+ discipline.
